    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-tom-yum-style-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>white cup mushrooms </strong>and<strong> red chilli[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Slice your <strong>garlic cloves</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-tom-yum-style-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>fish sauce</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>lemongrass and lime leaf paste,</strong> <strong>tomato paste</strong>, a squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span><strong> sugar </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tom yum-style sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-tom-yum-style-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>garlic slices</strong> cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the<strong> sliced white cup mushrooms</strong> for a further 2-3 min</p><p>drain then add your <strong>king prawns</strong> with <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>sliced chillies</strong></p><p>(save the rest for later!) and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-tom-yum-style-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked through, add the <strong>cooked rice </strong>and cook for 2-3 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-tom-yum-style-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tom yum-style sauce </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>King prawn</strong> <strong>tom yum-style rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-tom-yum-style-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/king-prawn-tom-yum-style-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>King prawn</strong> <strong>tom yum-style rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with your<strong> crispy onions</strong>, your remaining<strong> chilli slices </strong>and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
